[question]
How many bytes are there in a MAC address?
[/question]

workspace = 1in

[answer]
Given a MAC address such as: \verb+ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff+, each
hex value represents 4 bits.  Each group is 8 bits which is
one byte.  There are 6 groups so there are \textbf{8 bytes} or
\textbf{48 bits}.
[/answer]

